tags.name: The District
tags.note: The District at Southern Miss has acted as a gathering place since the founding of the university in 1910. Located in front of the Ogletree Alumni House in the southeast corner of campus, The District is the icon of Southern Miss heritage, tradition

tags.description: This smokestack has been here for many years. The city of Hattiesburg has constructed a park around it. Beyond the fact that it has been used as an incineratory, historical info about the stack's origin or purpose does not seem to be available.
